Over 3,000 candidates showed up for interviews demanding to be let inside the new Dr Pixley Ka-Isaka Seme Memorial Hospital in Durban. Following this, the provincial health department suspended the interview process. eNCA’s Lethiwe Mdluli reports. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - Thousands of candidates arrived for interviews at the new Dr Pixley Ka-Isaka Seme Memorial Hospital in Durban on Tuesday, claiming they were called for interviews. Nurses seeking employment shared their frustrations following the suspension of the recruitment process. The health department says only 250 candidates were called but unfortunately all those who applied decided to come. WATCH: Demands for KZN hospital to open Over 3,000 candidates showed up for interviews, demanding to be let inside the new hospital. Following this, the provincial health department suspended the interview process. * eNCA’s Lethiwe Mdluli reports.